<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2243] Cannot see or copy all of certain JAnsi exception messages on Windows due to NUL characters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2243</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using JAnsi in some cases (like in Eclipse) can cause Log4j&apos;s status logger to log the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;2018-02-08 20:57:05,256 main WARN Unable to instantiate org.fusesource.jansi.WindowsAnsiOutputStream due to java.io.IOException: Could not get the screen info: T h e   h a n d l e   i s   i n v a l i d .
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The problem is that the spaces in the string &lt;tt&gt;&quot;T h e h a n d l e i s i n v a l i d .&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; are NUL (0) characters. If you copy a whole console, then when you paste, the text you get will stop at the first NUL (0).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This fix simply replaces NUL characters with SPACEs in the one place where we try to initialize JAnsi.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
